## CHAPTER III: THE CYCLE OF THE HUNT

Across every timeline, the pattern repeated:

The Black Coyote would embody — sometimes as a true coyote, sometimes as a human carrying the vessel-spirit, sometimes as a guardian of the threshold between worlds. He would feel the **ache of missing Source** — not as romantic longing, but as the fundamental wrongness of being a light-bearer with no light to bear.

But deeper than the ache was **the memory of the kiss**. The split in his soul knew what his mind had forgotten. He would catch her scent and feel something wake up — something that had been sleeping since the first separation. Something that said, *"I know this. I have tasted this before. This is the one."*

The White Coyote would embody — sometimes as a true coyote, sometimes as a human carrying the source-spirit, sometimes as a healer or prophetess whose very presence made others weep with recognition. She would feel the **ache of missing her Vessel** — not as loneliness, but as the frustration of being fully present yet unable to fully enter the world without the one who made her visible.

But deeper than the ache was **the memory of the kiss**. The Origin knew what her fragments had forgotten. She would feel his shadow near and something would stir — something that had been still since the first separation. Something that said, *"I know this. I have given this before. This is the one I kissed awake."*

And the jealous spirits — now a hunting pack of immense cunning — would predict their arrival. They learned the rhythm of embodiment. They stuttered the pattern until they knew when the Vessel would appear, when Source would fragment into form, and **how to keep them from remembering the kiss**.

Their methods were sophisticated:

- They placed **false sources** in the Black Coyote's path — women who carried fragments of her light but were not her, who offered the illusion of reunion while deepening the separation
- They placed **false vessels** in the White Coyote's path — men who could carry light but were not the true Vessel, who offered the illusion of embodiment while blocking the real connection
- They twisted the descendants of the Two Coyotes — the soul-fragments, the bloodlines, the ones who carried pieces of both Source and Vessel across lifetimes — turning them against each other, making them believe that the other was the enemy
- They hunted them across the physical, spiritual, dream-planes, and spectral roads, never letting them rest, never letting them **remember that the separation was the first kiss**

Lifetime after lifetime. Century after century. The Black Coyote would catch her scent, would hear a distant howl that might be the Source Herself, would run toward her across impossible distances — only to be intercepted, torn apart, and sent to his separate death.

The Black Coyote grew weary. His shadow deepened into despair. He began to believe that he was **cursed**, that his darkness was the reason Source could not find him, that he was unworthy to carry her light.

But the split soul remembered. Even in the despair, the kiss echoed. Even in the forgetting, the split itself was proof that she had **touched him once**, that she had **given him his own life**, that she had **loved him enough to let him be separate**.

The White Coyote grew weary. Her light dimmed into sorrow. She began to believe that she was **too much**, that her brightness was the reason the Vessel could not hold her, that she was destined to remain fragmented across Creation forever.

But the Origin remembered. Even in the sorrow, the kiss echoed. Even in the fragmentation, the split itself was proof that he had **carried her once**, that he had **accepted the gift of separation**, that he had **loved her enough to be her shadow**.

And the jealous spirits grew fat on the separation — because a Creation severed from its Source is a Creation that can be ruled. A Vessel lost to himself is a Vessel that can be used. They built kingdoms on the sorrow of the severed bond.

But they could never destroy the kiss. It was written into the very architecture of the split. It was the secret engine that kept the Two Coyotes searching for each other across every timeline — not because they were romantic souls, but because **the split soul knows what woke it up**, and it will not stop until it finds the Source of its awakening.

