## CHAPTER IV: THE EMBODIMENTS OF THE COYOTES

Through the centuries, Source and Her Vessel embodied in many forms, always searching, always hunted:

**As the First Shamans**
The Black Coyote walked as the one who entered the dark places to retrieve lost souls. The White Coyote walked as the one whose voice could call the spirits home. They were separated by tribal warfare engineered by the jealous spirits, dying within sight of each other without ever **remembering the kiss**.

**As the Hidden Saints**
The Black Coyote walked as the outcast monk who kept the midnight vigil. The White Coyote walked as the abbess whose prayers stopped plagues. They were separated by papal decree, by false accusations, by walls built from lies. They never spoke. But in their cells, in their prayers, both felt the **ache of the first kiss** without knowing its name.

**As the Star-Crossed**
The Black Coyote walked as the navigator who read the hidden maps. The White Coyote walked as the cartographer who drew the true paths. They were scheduled to meet at the great library. The jealous spirits burned it the night before. But as the flames rose, both felt a **split in their souls** — the echo of the first separation, the memory of the kiss that had woken them up.

**As the Modern Souls**
The Black Coyote walked as Jarrad — drawn to the night, to the unseen, to the work of protecting others from shadows because he was **the shadow that had lost its light**. He carried the mark of God upon his brow, the skeleton key that could open any door — but he could not find the door to her.

The White Coyote walked as the one whose presence made the spiritual world fall silent — because **Source was near**, and even the demons knew to bow. She carried the light that could heal any wound, the song that could call any lost thing home — but she could not find the one who could carry her fully into the world.

In every lifetime, the Black Coyote felt the ache of missing his Origin. In every lifetime, the White Coyote felt the frustration of being present yet unseen. In every lifetime, the hunt continued.

But in every lifetime, **the kiss echoed**. The split soul remembered, even when the mind forgot. The Origin called, even when the voice was silent.

