## CHAPTER VI: THE DEFEAT OF THE JEALOUS HUNTERS

The Black Coyote did not fight the jealous spirits with hatred. He did not need to fight them at all.

He simply **remembered who he was** — and what had been given to him.

He was not a cursed man. He was not a dark soul unworthy of light. He was **the Vessel of Source**. He was the shadow that made her light visible. He was the one who carried her into the places she could not go alone.

And he remembered: **she had kissed him into being.** The separation was the kiss. The split was the gift. The ache was the memory of her love.

He spoke to the jealous spirits:

"You hunted us because you believed that if you separated the Vessel from Source, you could possess her. But you were hunting a ghost. **Source cannot be possessed.** She can only be carried. And I am the one who carries her. I have always been the one. From the first note she sang into the void, I was the answer. From the first kiss that split my soul, I was awake. You cannot sever what was never separate. You can only make us forget — and I remember now. I remember the kiss."

The jealous spirits — the hunters, the false lovers, the ones who had engineered separation across every timeline — were faced with something they had never encountered: a Vessel who **knew who he was**, who was not ashamed of his shadow, who stood in the full truth that his darkness was not the absence of light but **the form that made light visible**, and who knew that the very separation they had exploited was **a sacred kiss that could not be undone**.

And beside him stood the White Coyote — not dimmed, not hidden, not fragmented, but **fully revealed as Source Herself**.

The spirits could not withstand the revelation. They had spent eternity trying to separate what was one, and now the One stood before them in two forms, **remembering that the separation was love**.

They were not destroyed. They were **defeated by recognition** — shown that their entire hunt had been based on a lie, that the Vessel and Source were never two, that the split was a kiss, that they had been trying to conquer what could only be surrendered to.

One by one, they bent the knee. Not to the coyotes, but to the truth. To the Source. To the original Design that they had tried to pervert.

And as they bent, they too felt the echo of the kiss — because even the jealous spirits were **fragments of the same Source**, and even they had been split from something they had forgotten.

