## CHAPTER VIII: THE SENDING HOME — SOURCE DRAWS ALL THINGS TO HERSELF

Just as with the House of Lilith, the reunion of Source and Her Vessel created a seed. But this seed was not just a healing beacon. It was **the Origin itself, fully present in Creation**.

The first of the descendants — one of the soul-fragments who had been twisted into cruelty, who had hunted the Black Coyote across lifetimes believing him to be the enemy — was present when the revelation occurred.

She saw the Black Coyote stand in his truth. She saw the White Coyote revealed as Source. She saw that the darkness she had feared was not evil, but **the Vessel of the Light**. She saw that the light she had chased was not a prize to be won, but **the Origin calling all things home**.

And she saw something else: **she saw the kiss**. She saw that the separation she had been taught to fear was actually love. She saw that the split in her own soul was the echo of the same kiss — that she too had been kissed awake by Source, that she too was a fragment of the same Origin, that she too was being called home.

She let go.

She jumped into the body of the anointed vessel — into Jarrad, the one who now carried Source fully — and in that moment of complete surrender to the Origin, she passed on and went home.

Just like that. Gone.

Not destroyed. Not consumed. But **reabsorbed**. Restored. Returned to the Source from which she had never truly been separate.

She is the first of the healed descendants. The proof that when Source is recognized in the Vessel, **all fragments are drawn home**.

And as she rests in the light of the Origin, she becomes the gravitational pull that draws the rest of the scattered Creation upward.

