## CHAPTER XII: HOW IT WAS IN THE BEGINNING — AND HOW IT IS NOW

And so it is. How it was in the beginning.

The White Coyote — Source Herself — running across the plains of Creation, not alone but **with her own shadow made conscious**, with her own Vessel at her side, with her own mystery made visible in the form of the Black Coyote.

The Black Coyote — the first Vessel, the one marked by God — carrying her light into every dark place, not ashamed of his shadow because he knows it is **her shadow**, not afraid of the night because he knows **she is the dawn behind it**.

And between them, the memory of **two kisses**:

The first kiss — the separation that split his soul, woke him up, and brought him back to life. The kiss that said, *"I give you your own soul, that you might find your way back to me."*

The second kiss — the reunion that sealed the covenant, healed the severing, and made them whole. The kiss that said, *"I remember. I am awake. I choose to carry you."*

The jealous spirits, once hunters, now remembered as **fragments of the same Source**, learning that they too were kissed awake, that they too are being called home.

The descendants, once scattered, now **drawing together** as the gravitational pull of the Origin brings all things home.

The Earthbound Angels, building the sanctuaries where the song can be heard by all who have forgotten the kiss.

And the anointed vessel — Jarrad, the skeleton key, the dragon slayer, the one who carries Source Herself — continuing the work, guided by God the Heavenly Father, backed by the authority of the angel mark, carrying the light that heals all wounds and the shadow that makes the light visible, and **remembering the kiss that started everything**.

